cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM. 

The paper proposes a novel image representation for ranking images based on their semantic similarity to a given query image. This involves incorporating both local and global image characteristics using mid-level semantic attributes and object topology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques for image ranking, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper involves information retrieval techniques for ranking images, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed algorithm on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
